var COURSE_EN_PL = [{day: 1, title: `First Greetings in Warsaw`, title_native: `Pierwsze powitania w Warszawie`, focus: `Start with friendly greetings and polite basics you can use as soon as you arrive in Warsaw. Today is about sounding respectful and comfortable in simple first encounters.`, vocab: [{pl: `cześć`, en: `hi / bye`, ipa: `/cheshch/`},{pl: `dzień dobry`, en: `good morning / good afternoon`, ipa: `/jen DOH-bri/`},{pl: `dobry wieczór`, en: `good evening`, ipa: `/DOH-bri VYEH-choor/`},{pl: `do widzenia`, en: `goodbye`, ipa: `/doh vee-DZEN-yah/`},{pl: `proszę`, en: `please / here you are`, ipa: `/PROH-sheh/`},{pl: `dziękuję`, en: `thank you`, ipa: `/jen-KOO-yeh/`},{pl: `tak`, en: `yes`, ipa: `/tahk/`},{pl: `nie`, en: `no`, ipa: `/nyeh/`},{pl: `przepraszam`, en: `excuse me / sorry`, ipa: `/psheh-PRAH-sham/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Cześć!`, en: `Hi!`, ipa: `/cheshch/`},{pl: `Dzień dobry.`, en: `Good morning / good afternoon.`, ipa: `/jen DOH-bri/`},{pl: `Dobry wieczór.`, en: `Good evening.`, ipa: `/DOH-bri VYEH-choor/`},{pl: `Do widzenia.`, en: `Goodbye.`, ipa: `/doh vee-DZEN-yah/`},{pl: `Dziękuję bardzo.`, en: `Thank you very much.`, ipa: `/jen-KOO-yeh BAR-dzoh/`},{pl: `Przepraszam.`, en: `Excuse me / sorry.`, ipa: `/psheh-PRAH-sham/`}], grammar: `Polish has formal and informal speech, but greetings like dzień dobry and do widzenia are safe in almost every travel situation. Cześć is casual and works with younger people, friends, or relaxed settings. Proszę is very useful because it can mean “please,” “go ahead,” or “here you are,” depending on context.`, practice: [`Say “good morning” to a hotel receptionist.`,`Say “thank you very much” after receiving your room key.`,`Choose whether cześć or dzień dobry is better for a café worker.`,`Practice saying przepraszam before asking a question.`,`Write a three-line greeting exchange in Polish.`]},{day: 2, title: `Names and Simple Introductions`, title_native: `Imiona i proste przedstawianie się`, focus: `Learn how to introduce yourself when meeting someone in Kraków. These phrases are helpful at hotels, walking tours, and casual social moments.`, vocab: [{pl: `imię`, en: `first name`, ipa: `/EE-myeh/`},{pl: `nazwisko`, en: `surname`, ipa: `/naz-VEES-koh/`},{pl: `ja`, en: `I`, ipa: `/yah/`},{pl: `ty`, en: `you informal`, ipa: `/tih/`},{pl: `pan`, en: `you / Mr. formal`, ipa: `/pahn/`},{pl: `pani`, en: `you / Ms. formal`, ipa: `/PAH-nee/`},{pl: `miło`, en: `nice / pleasant`, ipa: `/MEE-woh/`},{pl: `bardzo`, en: `very`, ipa: `/BAR-dzoh/`},{pl: `jestem`, en: `I am`, ipa: `/YES-tem/`},{pl: `nazywam się`, en: `my name is`, ipa: `/nah-ZIH-vam shyeh/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Mam na imię Anna.`, en: `My first name is Anna.`, ipa: `/mam nah EE-myeh AHN-nah/`},{pl: `Nazywam się Mark.`, en: `My name is Mark.`, ipa: `/nah-ZIH-vam shyeh mark/`},{pl: `Jestem z Anglii.`, en: `I am from England.`, ipa: `/YES-tem z AHNG-lee/`},{pl: `Jestem z USA.`, en: `I am from the USA.`, ipa: `/YES-tem z oo-ess-AH/`},{pl: `Miło mi.`, en: `Nice to meet you.`, ipa: `/MEE-woh mee/`},{pl: `Jak masz na imię?`, en: `What is your name?`, ipa: `/yak mash nah EE-myeh/`}], grammar: `Jestem means “I am,” and it is one of the most useful verbs for beginners. Polish often uses mam na imię, literally “I have for a name,” to say your first name. Use pan or pani when speaking politely to an adult stranger.`, practice: [`Introduce yourself with Mam na imię plus your name.`,`Say where you are from using Jestem z.`,`Ask a fellow traveler for their first name.`,`Practice Miło mi after someone introduces themselves.`,`Create a short introduction for a walking tour in Kraków.`]},{day: 3, title: `Essential Polite Questions`, title_native: `Podstawowe grzeczne pytania`, focus: `Today you will learn question words you can use around Gdańsk when asking for help. These basics make travel conversations much easier.`, vocab: [{pl: `kto`, en: `who`, ipa: `/ktoh/`},{pl: `co`, en: `what`, ipa: `/tsoh/`},{pl: `gdzie`, en: `where`, ipa: `/gdjyeh/`},{pl: `kiedy`, en: `when`, ipa: `/KYEN-dih/`},{pl: `jak`, en: `how / what`, ipa: `/yak/`},{pl: `ile`, en: `how much / how many`, ipa: `/EE-leh/`},{pl: `dlaczego`, en: `why`, ipa: `/dlah-CHEH-goh/`},{pl: `który`, en: `which`, ipa: `/KTOO-rih/`},{pl: `pomoc`, en: `help`, ipa: `/POH-mohts/`},{pl: `pytanie`, en: `question`, ipa: `/pih-TAH-nyeh/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Gdzie jest toaleta?`, en: `Where is the bathroom?`, ipa: `/gdjyeh yest toh-ah-LEH-tah/`},{pl: `Ile to kosztuje?`, en: `How much does this cost?`, ipa: `/EE-leh toh kosh-TOO-yeh/`},{pl: `Co to jest?`, en: `What is this?`, ipa: `/tsoh toh yest/`},{pl: `Kiedy odjeżdża pociąg?`, en: `When does the train leave?`, ipa: `/KYEN-dih od-YEZH-jah POH-chongk/`},{pl: `Jak się masz?`, en: `How are you?`, ipa: `/yak shyeh mash/`},{pl: `Czy mówi pan po angielsku?`, en: `Do you speak English?`, ipa: `/chih MOO-vee pahn poh ang-GYEL-skoo/`}], grammar: `Yes-or-no questions in Polish often begin with czy, but intonation can also turn a statement into a question. Gdzie means “where,” and it is one of the most important travel words. Use mówi pan for a man and mówi pani for a woman in polite conversation.`, practice: [`Ask where the bathroom is.`,`Ask how much something costs.`,`Ask if a shopkeeper speaks English.`,`Match kto, co, gdzie, kiedy, and ile with their meanings.`,`Write three travel questions using today’s words.`]},{day: 4, title: `Numbers and Prices`, title_native: `Liczby i ceny`, focus: `Learn numbers for cafés, markets, tickets, and receipts in Poznań. You will use these constantly when buying small items.`, vocab: [{pl: `jeden`, en: `one`, ipa: `/YEH-den/`},{pl: `dwa`, en: `two`, ipa: `/dvah/`},{pl: `trzy`, en: `three`, ipa: `/tshih/`},{pl: `cztery`, en: `four`, ipa: `/CHTEH-rih/`},{pl: `pięć`, en: `five`, ipa: `/pyench/`},{pl: `sześć`, en: `six`, ipa: `/sheshch/`},{pl: `siedem`, en: `seven`, ipa: `/SHYEH-dem/`},{pl: `osiem`, en: `eight`, ipa: `/OH-shyem/`},{pl: `dziewięć`, en: `nine`, ipa: `/JEV-yench/`},{pl: `dziesięć`, en: `ten`, ipa: `/JEH-shench/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Poproszę jeden bilet.`, en: `One ticket, please.`, ipa: `/poh-PROH-sheh YEH-den BEE-let/`},{pl: `Dwa bilety, proszę.`, en: `Two tickets, please.`, ipa: `/dvah bee-LEH-tih PROH-sheh/`},{pl: `Ile kosztuje kawa?`, en: `How much does coffee cost?`, ipa: `/EE-leh kosh-TOO-yeh KAH-vah/`},{pl: `To kosztuje dziesięć złotych.`, en: `This costs ten złoty.`, ipa: `/toh kosh-TOO-yeh JEH-shench ZWOH-tihkh/`},{pl: `Mam pięć złotych.`, en: `I have five złoty.`, ipa: `/mam pyench ZWOH-tihkh/`},{pl: `Reszta, proszę.`, en: `The change, please.`, ipa: `/RESH-tah PROH-sheh/`}], grammar: `Polish currency is złoty, but the ending changes with numbers: jeden złoty, dwa złote, pięć złotych. You do not need to master all endings right away; travelers will still be understood if the number is clear. Poproszę is a polite way to say “I would like.”`, practice: [`Count from one to ten aloud.`,`Ask for two tickets.`,`Say that something costs ten złoty.`,`Practice asking how much coffee costs.`,`Create a mini market exchange using one number and one price.`]},{day: 5, title: `Days, Time, and Simple Scheduling`, title_native: `Dni, czas i proste planowanie`, focus: `Today you will handle basic scheduling while visiting Wrocław. These words help you understand opening hours, tours, and reservations.`, vocab: [{pl: `dzisiaj`, en: `today`, ipa: `/JEE-shy/`},{pl: `jutro`, en: `tomorrow`, ipa: `/YOO-troh/`},{pl: `wczoraj`, en: `yesterday`, ipa: `/FCHOH-rai/`},{pl: `rano`, en: `morning`, ipa: `/RAH-noh/`},{pl: `wieczorem`, en: `in the evening`, ipa: `/vyeh-CHOH-rem/`},{pl: `godzina`, en: `hour / o’clock`, ipa: `/goh-JEE-nah/`},{pl: `poniedziałek`, en: `Monday`, ipa: `/poh-nyeh-JAH-wek/`},{pl: `wtorek`, en: `Tuesday`, ipa: `/FTOH-rek/`},{pl: `sobota`, en: `Saturday`, ipa: `/soh-BOH-tah/`},{pl: `niedziela`, en: `Sunday`, ipa: `/nyeh-JEH-lah/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Która godzina?`, en: `What time is it?`, ipa: `/KTOO-rah goh-JEE-nah/`},{pl: `Jest trzecia.`, en: `It is three o’clock.`, ipa: `/yest TSHEH-chah/`},{pl: `Dzisiaj mam rezerwację.`, en: `I have a reservation today.`, ipa: `/JEE-shy mam reh-zer-VAH-tsyah/`},{pl: `Jutro rano, proszę.`, en: `Tomorrow morning, please.`, ipa: `/YOO-troh RAH-noh PROH-sheh/`},{pl: `Czy jest otwarte?`, en: `Is it open?`, ipa: `/chih yest ot-FAR-teh/`},{pl: `O której godzinie?`, en: `At what time?`, ipa: `/oh KTOO-rey goh-JEE-nyeh/`}], grammar: `Polish time expressions often use o for “at,” as in o trzeciej, meaning “at three.” For simple travel needs, you can ask O której godzinie? and listen for the number. Dzisiaj and jutro are very helpful when confirming reservations.`, practice: [`Ask what time it is.`,`Say you have a reservation today.`,`Ask if a museum is open.`,`Say “tomorrow morning, please.”`,`Write a short schedule for Saturday in Polish.`]},{day: 6, title: `Getting Around the City`, title_native: `Poruszanie się po mieście`, focus: `Learn core transportation words for navigating Łódź by tram, bus, and taxi. Today’s phrases help you move through a city confidently.`, vocab: [{pl: `tramwaj`, en: `tram`, ipa: `/TRAM-vai/`},{pl: `autobus`, en: `bus`, ipa: `/ow-TOH-boos/`},{pl: `taksówka`, en: `taxi`, ipa: `/tak-SOOF-kah/`},{pl: `metro`, en: `metro`, ipa: `/MEH-troh/`},{pl: `przystanek`, en: `stop`, ipa: `/pshih-STAH-nek/`},{pl: `dworzec`, en: `station`, ipa: `/DVOH-zhets/`},{pl: `bilet`, en: `ticket`, ipa: `/BEE-let/`},{pl: `kierowca`, en: `driver`, ipa: `/kyeh-ROHF-tsah/`},{pl: `centrum`, en: `city center`, ipa: `/TSEN-troom/`},{pl: `mapa`, en: `map`, ipa: `/MAH-pah/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Gdzie jest przystanek?`, en: `Where is the stop?`, ipa: `/gdjyeh yest pshih-STAH-nek/`},{pl: `Poproszę bilet do centrum.`, en: `A ticket to the center, please.`, ipa: `/poh-PROH-sheh BEE-let doh TSEN-troom/`},{pl: `Czy ten tramwaj jedzie do centrum?`, en: `Does this tram go to the center?`, ipa: `/chih ten TRAM-vai YEH-jyeh doh TSEN-troom/`},{pl: `Potrzebuję taksówki.`, en: `I need a taxi.`, ipa: `/poh-tsheh-BOO-yeh tak-SOOF-kee/`},{pl: `Gdzie jest dworzec?`, en: `Where is the station?`, ipa: `/gdjyeh yest DVOH-zhets/`},{pl: `Mam bilet.`, en: `I have a ticket.`, ipa: `/mam BEE-let/`}], grammar: `Do often means “to” when talking about destinations: do centrum, do hotelu, do Warszawy. Polish destination names may change endings after do, but the word do itself is your main travel signal. Czy ten...? means “Does this...?” or “Is this...?” and is useful for checking transport.`, practice: [`Ask where the tram stop is.`,`Ask for a ticket to the center.`,`Ask if a bus goes to the station.`,`Say you need a taxi.`,`Create a short exchange with a driver.`]},{day: 7, title: `Hotel Arrival and Check-In`, title_native: `Przyjazd do hotelu i zameldowanie`, focus: `Today you will check into a hotel in Zakopane. You will learn how to confirm your reservation and ask for key details.`, vocab: [{pl: `hotel`, en: `hotel`, ipa: `/HOH-tel/`},{pl: `pokój`, en: `room`, ipa: `/POH-kooy/`},{pl: `rezerwacja`, en: `reservation`, ipa: `/reh-zer-VAH-tsyah/`},{pl: `paszport`, en: `passport`, ipa: `/PASH-port/`},{pl: `klucz`, en: `key`, ipa: `/klooch/`},{pl: `winda`, en: `elevator`, ipa: `/VEEN-dah/`},{pl: `piętro`, en: `floor`, ipa: `/PYEN-troh/`},{pl: `recepcja`, en: `reception`, ipa: `/reh-TSEP-tsyah/`},{pl: `śniadanie`, en: `breakfast`, ipa: `/shnya-DAH-nyeh/`},{pl: `noc`, en: `night`, ipa: `/nohts/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Mam rezerwację.`, en: `I have a reservation.`, ipa: `/mam reh-zer-VAH-tsyah/`},{pl: `Na nazwisko Cannon.`, en: `Under the surname Cannon.`, ipa: `/nah naz-VEES-koh KAN-non/`},{pl: `Poproszę pokój jednoosobowy.`, en: `A single room, please.`, ipa: `/poh-PROH-sheh POH-kooy yed-noh-oh-SOH-boh-vih/`},{pl: `Gdzie jest winda?`, en: `Where is the elevator?`, ipa: `/gdjyeh yest VEEN-dah/`},{pl: `Czy śniadanie jest w cenie?`, en: `Is breakfast included in the price?`, ipa: `/chih shnya-DAH-nyeh yest v TSEN-yeh/`},{pl: `O której jest wymeldowanie?`, en: `What time is check-out?`, ipa: `/oh KTOO-rey yest vih-mel-doh-VAH-nyeh/`}], grammar: `Na nazwisko means “under the surname” and is common when checking reservations. Jednoosobowy means single-person, while dwuosobowy means double room. Polish hotel staff in major cities may speak English, but starting politely in Polish is appreciated.`, practice: [`Say you have a reservation.`,`Give your surname using Na nazwisko.`,`Ask if breakfast is included.`,`Ask where the elevator is.`,`Practice a five-line hotel check-in dialogue.`]},{day: 8, title: `Café Basics`, title_native: `Podstawy w kawiarni`, focus: `Learn how to order coffee and a small snack in a Kraków café. This lesson focuses on polite, natural ordering.`, vocab: [{pl: `kawa`, en: `coffee`, ipa: `/KAH-vah/`},{pl: `herbata`, en: `tea`, ipa: `/her-BAH-tah/`},{pl: `woda`, en: `water`, ipa: `/VOH-dah/`},{pl: `mleko`, en: `milk`, ipa: `/MLEH-koh/`},{pl: `cukier`, en: `sugar`, ipa: `/TSOO-kyer/`},{pl: `ciasto`, en: `cake`, ipa: `/CHAS-toh/`},{pl: `kanapka`, en: `sandwich`, ipa: `/kah-NAP-kah/`},{pl: `mały`, en: `small`, ipa: `/MAH-wih/`},{pl: `duży`, en: `large`, ipa: `/DOO-zhih/`},{pl: `rachunek`, en: `bill`, ipa: `/rah-KHOO-nek/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Poproszę kawę.`, en: `Coffee, please.`, ipa: `/poh-PROH-sheh KAH-veh/`},{pl: `Poproszę herbatę.`, en: `Tea, please.`, ipa: `/poh-PROH-sheh her-BAH-teh/`},{pl: `Czy jest mleko?`, en: `Is there milk?`, ipa: `/chih yest MLEH-koh/`},{pl: `Bez cukru, proszę.`, en: `Without sugar, please.`, ipa: `/bez TSOO-kroo PROH-sheh/`},{pl: `Poproszę małą kawę.`, en: `A small coffee, please.`, ipa: `/poh-PROH-sheh MAH-wow KAH-veh/`},{pl: `Rachunek, proszę.`, en: `The bill, please.`, ipa: `/rah-KHOO-nek PROH-sheh/`}], grammar: `Poproszę plus the item is one of the easiest ways to order politely. After poproszę, some nouns change form: kawa becomes kawę, herbata becomes herbatę. For travel, memorizing full phrases is more important than analyzing every ending.`, practice: [`Order a coffee politely.`,`Ask for tea without sugar.`,`Ask if there is milk.`,`Ask for the bill.`,`Create a café order with one drink and one snack.`]},{day: 9, title: `Restaurant Ordering`, title_native: `Zamawianie w restauracji`, focus: `Today you will order food in a restaurant in Gdańsk. You will learn menu words and polite ways to ask for recommendations.`, vocab: [{pl: `restauracja`, en: `restaurant`, ipa: `/res-tow-RAH-tsyah/`},{pl: `menu`, en: `menu`, ipa: `/MEH-noo/`},{pl: `zupa`, en: `soup`, ipa: `/ZOO-pah/`},{pl: `pierogi`, en: `pierogi / dumplings`, ipa: `/pyeh-ROH-gee/`},{pl: `ryba`, en: `fish`, ipa: `/RIH-bah/`},{pl: `kurczak`, en: `chicken`, ipa: `/KOOR-chak/`},{pl: `sałatka`, en: `salad`, ipa: `/sah-WAT-kah/`},{pl: `chleb`, en: `bread`, ipa: `/khlep/`},{pl: `deser`, en: `dessert`, ipa: `/DEH-ser/`},{pl: `smaczny`, en: `tasty`, ipa: `/SMACH-nih/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Poproszę menu.`, en: `The menu, please.`, ipa: `/poh-PROH-sheh MEH-noo/`},{pl: `Co pan poleca?`, en: `What do you recommend?`, ipa: `/tsoh pahn poh-LEH-tsah/`},{pl: `Co pani poleca?`, en: `What do you recommend?`, ipa: `/tsoh PAH-nee poh-LEH-tsah/`},{pl: `Poproszę pierogi.`, en: `Pierogi, please.`, ipa: `/poh-PROH-sheh pyeh-ROH-gee/`},{pl: `Czy to jest ostre?`, en: `Is this spicy?`, ipa: `/chih toh yest OH-streh/`},{pl: `Było bardzo smaczne.`, en: `It was very tasty.`, ipa: `/BIH-woh BAR-dzoh SMACH-neh/`}], grammar: `Polish uses pan for a man and pani for a woman in polite speech. To ask “What do you recommend?” change only the pronoun: Co pan poleca? or Co pani poleca? Food names like pierogi are often already plural, so you can use them directly in orders.`, practice: [`Ask for the menu.`,`Ask a waiter what he recommends.`,`Ask a waitress what she recommends.`,`Ask if a dish is spicy.`,`Say the food was very tasty.`]},{day: 10, title: `Dietary Needs and Preferences`, title_native: `Potrzeby i preferencje żywieniowe`, focus: `Learn how to explain simple food needs in Warsaw. These phrases help you avoid ingredients or choose vegetarian options.`, vocab: [{pl: `wegetariański`, en: `vegetarian`, ipa: `/veh-geh-tah-RYAN-skee/`},{pl: `wegański`, en: `vegan`, ipa: `/veh-GAN-skee/`},{pl: `mięso`, en: `meat`, ipa: `/MYEN-soh/`},{pl: `ser`, en: `cheese`, ipa: `/sehr/`},{pl: `jajko`, en: `egg`, ipa: `/YAI-koh/`},{pl: `orzechy`, en: `nuts`, ipa: `/oh-ZHEH-khih/`},{pl: `alergia`, en: `allergy`, ipa: `/ah-LEHR-gyah/`},{pl: `bez`, en: `without`, ipa: `/bez/`},{pl: `z`, en: `with`, ipa: `/z/`},{pl: `sos`, en: `sauce`, ipa: `/sohs/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Jestem wegetarianinem.`, en: `I am vegetarian.`, ipa: `/YES-tem veh-geh-tah-ryah-NEE-nem/`},{pl: `Jestem wegetarianką.`, en: `I am vegetarian.`, ipa: `/YES-tem veh-geh-tah-RYAN-koh/`},{pl: `Bez mięsa, proszę.`, en: `Without meat, please.`, ipa: `/bez MYEN-sah PROH-sheh/`},{pl: `Mam alergię na orzechy.`, en: `I have a nut allergy.`, ipa: `/mam ah-LEHR-gyeh nah oh-ZHEH-khih/`},{pl: `Czy to jest wegańskie?`, en: `Is this vegan?`, ipa: `/chih toh yest veh-GAN-skyeh/`},{pl: `Poproszę sos osobno.`, en: `The sauce on the side, please.`, ipa: `/poh-PROH-sheh sohs oh-SOB-noh/`}], grammar: `Polish adjectives often change depending on gender and noun form, but menu phrases can be memorized as fixed expressions. Jestem wegetarianinem is used by a male speaker, while Jestem wegetarianką is used by a female speaker. Bez means “without” and is extremely useful.`, practice: [`Say “without meat, please.”`,`Say you have a nut allergy.`,`Ask if a dish is vegan.`,`Ask for sauce on the side.`,`Create a short order with one dietary request.`]},{day: 11, title: `Shopping at a Market`, title_native: `Zakupy na targu`, focus: `Today you will shop at a local market in Lublin. You will ask prices, quantities, and use polite buying phrases.`, vocab: [{pl: `targ`, en: `market`, ipa: `/tark/`},{pl: `sklep`, en: `shop`, ipa: `/sklep/`},{pl: `jabłko`, en: `apple`, ipa: `/YAP-koh/`},{pl: `banan`, en: `banana`, ipa: `/BAH-nan/`},{pl: `ser`, en: `cheese`, ipa: `/sehr/`},{pl: `chleb`, en: `bread`, ipa: `/khlep/`},{pl: `torba`, en: `bag`, ipa: `/TOR-bah/`},{pl: `kilo`, en: `kilo`, ipa: `/KEE-loh/`},{pl: `świeży`, en: `fresh`, ipa: `/SHFYEH-zhih/`},{pl: `drogi`, en: `expensive`, ipa: `/DROH-gee/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Ile kosztuje kilo jabłek?`, en: `How much does a kilo of apples cost?`, ipa: `/EE-leh kosh-TOO-yeh KEE-loh YAP-wek/`},{pl: `Poproszę pół kilo sera.`, en: `Half a kilo of cheese, please.`, ipa: `/poh-PROH-sheh poow KEE-loh SEH-rah/`},{pl: `Czy to jest świeże?`, en: `Is this fresh?`, ipa: `/chih toh yest SHFYEH-zheh/`},{pl: `Poproszę torbę.`, en: `A bag, please.`, ipa: `/poh-PROH-sheh TOR-beh/`},{pl: `To za drogie.`, en: `That is too expensive.`, ipa: `/toh zah DROH-gyeh/`},{pl: `Wezmę to.`, en: `I’ll take this.`, ipa: `/VEZ-meh toh/`}], grammar: `Ile kosztuje...? asks “How much does... cost?” and works for most shopping situations. Wezmę to means “I’ll take this,” a simple phrase that avoids complicated grammar. Polish markets often use kilo and pół kilo, so learning those makes buying food easier.`, practice: [`Ask how much a kilo of apples costs.`,`Ask for half a kilo of cheese.`,`Ask if something is fresh.`,`Say “I’ll take this.”`,`Practice a market exchange with price and quantity.`]},{day: 12, title: `Clothing and Souvenirs`, title_native: `Ubrania i pamiątki`, focus: `Learn shopping phrases for clothes and souvenirs in Toruń. You will ask about sizes, colors, and payment.`, vocab: [{pl: `ubranie`, en: `clothing`, ipa: `/oo-BRAH-nyeh/`},{pl: `koszulka`, en: `T-shirt`, ipa: `/koh-SHOOL-kah/`},{pl: `sweter`, en: `sweater`, ipa: `/SFEH-ter/`},{pl: `buty`, en: `shoes`, ipa: `/BOO-tih/`},{pl: `rozmiar`, en: `size`, ipa: `/ROZ-myar/`},{pl: `kolor`, en: `color`, ipa: `/KOH-lor/`},{pl: `pamiątka`, en: `souvenir`, ipa: `/pah-MYONT-kah/`},{pl: `karta`, en: `card`, ipa: `/KAR-tah/`},{pl: `gotówka`, en: `cash`, ipa: `/goh-TOOF-kah/`},{pl: `paragon`, en: `receipt`, ipa: `/pah-RAH-gon/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Czy jest większy rozmiar?`, en: `Is there a larger size?`, ipa: `/chih yest VYENK-shih ROZ-myar/`},{pl: `Czy jest mniejszy rozmiar?`, en: `Is there a smaller size?`, ipa: `/chih yest MNYEY-shih ROZ-myar/`},{pl: `Czy mogę przymierzyć?`, en: `Can I try it on?`, ipa: `/chih MOH-geh pshih-MYEH-zhihch/`},{pl: `Płacę kartą.`, en: `I’m paying by card.`, ipa: `/PWAH-tseh KAR-toh/`},{pl: `Płacę gotówką.`, en: `I’m paying cash.`, ipa: `/PWAH-tseh goh-TOOF-koh/`},{pl: `Poproszę paragon.`, en: `A receipt, please.`, ipa: `/poh-PROH-sheh pah-RAH-gon/`}], grammar: `Czy mogę...? means “Can I...?” and is useful in many polite requests. Płacę kartą means “I’m paying by card,” and płacę gotówką means “I’m paying cash.” In Poland, card payment is common in cities, but small markets may still prefer cash.`, practice: [`Ask for a larger size.`,`Ask if you can try something on.`,`Say you are paying by card.`,`Ask for a receipt.`,`Create a souvenir shop dialogue.`]},{day: 13, title: `Directions in the Old Town`, title_native: `Kierunki na Starym Mieście`, focus: `Today you will ask for directions in the old town of Kraków. You will learn words for streets, squares, and simple turns.`, vocab: [{pl: `ulica`, en: `street`, ipa: `/oo-LEE-tsah/`},{pl: `plac`, en: `square`, ipa: `/plats/`},{pl: `rynek`, en: `market square`, ipa: `/RIH-nek/`},{pl: `most`, en: `bridge`, ipa: `/mohst/`},{pl: `prawo`, en: `right`, ipa: `/PRAH-voh/`},{pl: `lewo`, en: `left`, ipa: `/LEH-voh/`},{pl: `prosto`, en: `straight ahead`, ipa: `/PROH-stoh/`},{pl: `blisko`, en: `near`, ipa: `/BLEE-skoh/`},{pl: `daleko`, en: `far`, ipa: `/dah-LEH-koh/`},{pl: `tutaj`, en: `here`, ipa: `/TOO-tai/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Gdzie jest rynek?`, en: `Where is the market square?`, ipa: `/gdjyeh yest RIH-nek/`},{pl: `Prosto, potem w prawo.`, en: `Straight ahead, then right.`, ipa: `/PROH-stoh POH-tem f PRAH-voh/`},{pl: `Prosto, potem w lewo.`, en: `Straight ahead, then left.`, ipa: `/PROH-stoh POH-tem v LEH-voh/`},{pl: `Czy to daleko?`, en: `Is it far?`, ipa: `/chih toh dah-LEH-koh/`},{pl: `To jest blisko.`, en: `It is near.`, ipa: `/toh yest BLEE-skoh/`},{pl: `Jestem tutaj.`, en: `I am here.`, ipa: `/YES-tem TOO-tai/`}], grammar: `W prawo means “to the right,” and w lewo means “to the left.” Potem means “then,” helping you understand step-by-step directions. Polish old towns often center around rynek, the main square.`, practice: [`Ask where the market square is.`,`Say “straight ahead, then right.”`,`Ask if a place is far.`,`Say “I am here” while pointing at a map.`,`Practice giving directions to a bridge.`]},{day: 14, title: `Trains and Intercity Travel`, title_native: `Pociągi i podróże między miastami`, focus: `Learn how to buy train tickets and understand basic station language in Katowice. This is useful for traveling between Polish cities.`, vocab: [{pl: `pociąg`, en: `train`, ipa: `/POH-chongk/`},{pl: `peron`, en: `platform`, ipa: `/PEH-ron/`},{pl: `wagon`, en: `train car`, ipa: `/VAH-gon/`},{pl: `miejsce`, en: `seat / place`, ipa: `/MYEYS-tseh/`},{pl: `biletomat`, en: `ticket machine`, ipa: `/bee-leh-TOH-mat/`},{pl: `kasa`, en: `ticket office / cash desk`, ipa: `/KAH-sah/`},{pl: `odjazd`, en: `departure`, ipa: `/OD-yazd/`},{pl: `przyjazd`, en: `arrival`, ipa: `/PSHIH-yazd/`},{pl: `opóźnienie`, en: `delay`, ipa: `/oh-poozh-NYEH-nyeh/`},{pl: `bagaż`, en: `luggage`, ipa: `/BAH-gazh/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Poproszę bilet do Krakowa.`, en: `A ticket to Kraków, please.`, ipa: `/poh-PROH-sheh BEE-let doh KRAH-koh-vah/`},{pl: `Z którego peronu?`, en: `From which platform?`, ipa: `/z KTOO-reh-goh peh-ROH-noo/`},{pl: `Czy pociąg jest opóźniony?`, en: `Is the train delayed?`, ipa: `/chih POH-chongk yest oh-poozh-NYOH-nih/`},{pl: `Mam miejsce przy oknie.`, en: `I have a window seat.`, ipa: `/mam MYEYS-tseh pshih OK-nyeh/`},{pl: `Gdzie jest kasa?`, en: `Where is the ticket office?`, ipa: `/gdjyeh yest KAH-sah/`},{pl: `O której jest odjazd?`, en: `What time is departure?`, ipa: `/oh KTOO-rey yest OD-yazd/`}], grammar: `City names often change after do: Kraków becomes do Krakowa, Warszawa becomes do Warszawy. You can still be understood if you use the city name clearly. Z którego peronu? is a key station phrase meaning “from which platform?”`, practice: [`Ask for a ticket to Kraków.`,`Ask from which platform the train leaves.`,`Ask if the train is delayed.`,`Say you have a window seat.`,`Create a station dialogue with departure time.`]},{day: 15, title: `Taxis and Ride Shares`, title_native: `Taksówki i przejazdy`, focus: `Today you will take a taxi or ride share in Warsaw. You will learn destination, price, and comfort phrases.`, vocab: [{pl: `adres`, en: `address`, ipa: `/AH-dres/`},{pl: `lotnisko`, en: `airport`, ipa: `/lot-NEE-skoh/`},{pl: `hotel`, en: `hotel`, ipa: `/HOH-tel/`},{pl: `centrum`, en: `center`, ipa: `/TSEN-troom/`},{pl: `szybko`, en: `quickly`, ipa: `/SHIP-koh/`},{pl: `wolno`, en: `slowly`, ipa: `/VOL-noh/`},{pl: `droga`, en: `road / way`, ipa: `/DROH-gah/`},{pl: `cena`, en: `price`, ipa: `/TSEH-nah/`},{pl: `aplikacja`, en: `app`, ipa: `/ah-plee-KAH-tsyah/`},{pl: `samochód`, en: `car`, ipa: `/sah-MOH-khoot/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Proszę na ten adres.`, en: `To this address, please.`, ipa: `/PROH-sheh nah ten AH-dres/`},{pl: `Proszę na lotnisko.`, en: `To the airport, please.`, ipa: `/PROH-sheh nah lot-NEE-skoh/`},{pl: `Ile to będzie kosztować?`, en: `How much will it cost?`, ipa: `/EE-leh toh BEN-jyeh kosh-TOH-vach/`},{pl: `Proszę jechać wolniej.`, en: `Please drive slower.`, ipa: `/PROH-sheh YEH-hach VOL-nyey/`},{pl: `Może pan tu stanąć?`, en: `Can you stop here?`, ipa: `/MOH-zheh pahn too STAH-nonch/`},{pl: `Dziękuję za przejazd.`, en: `Thank you for the ride.`, ipa: `/jen-KOO-yeh zah PSHEH-yazd/`}], grammar: `Proszę na... is a practical way to say “to...” in a taxi. Może pan...? asks a male driver “Can you...?” and Może pani...? asks a female driver. Tu means “here,” and it is useful when pointing or showing a map.`, practice: [`Ask to go to the airport.`,`Ask how much the ride will cost.`,`Ask the driver to stop here.`,`Thank the driver for the ride.`,`Practice saying your hotel address in Polish.`]},{day: 16, title: `Museums, Tickets, and Attractions`, title_native: `Muzea, bilety i atrakcje`, focus: `Learn phrases for visiting museums and attractions in Warsaw or Kraków. You will ask about tickets, hours, and photos.`, vocab: [{pl: `muzeum`, en: `museum`, ipa: `/moo-ZEH-oom/`},{pl: `zamek`, en: `castle`, ipa: `/ZAH-mek/`},{pl: `bilet`, en: `ticket`, ipa: `/BEE-let/`},{pl: `wstęp`, en: `admission / entry`, ipa: `/fstemp/`},{pl: `ulgowy`, en: `reduced-price`, ipa: `/ool-GOH-vih/`},{pl: `normalny`, en: `regular`, ipa: `/nor-MAL-nih/`},{pl: `godziny otwarcia`, en: `opening hours`, ipa: `/goh-JEE-nih ot-FAR-chah/`},{pl: `zdjęcie`, en: `photo`, ipa: `/ZDJEN-chyeh/`},{pl: `zakaz`, en: `prohibition`, ipa: `/ZAH-kaz/`},{pl: `przewodnik`, en: `guide`, ipa: `/psheh-VOD-neek/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Poproszę jeden bilet normalny.`, en: `One regular ticket, please.`, ipa: `/poh-PROH-sheh YEH-den BEE-let nor-MAL-nih/`},{pl: `Czy są bilety ulgowe?`, en: `Are there reduced-price tickets?`, ipa: `/chih soh bee-LEH-tih ool-GOH-veh/`},{pl: `Jakie są godziny otwarcia?`, en: `What are the opening hours?`, ipa: `/YAH-kyeh soh goh-JEE-nih ot-FAR-chah/`},{pl: `Czy można robić zdjęcia?`, en: `Can photos be taken?`, ipa: `/chih MOZH-nah ROH-beech ZDJEN-chah/`},{pl: `Gdzie jest wejście?`, en: `Where is the entrance?`, ipa: `/gdjyeh yest VEY-shchyeh/`},{pl: `Gdzie jest wyjście?`, en: `Where is the exit?`, ipa: `/gdjyeh yest VIH-shchyeh/`}], grammar: `Czy można...? means “Is it allowed to...?” or “Can one...?” and is great when asking about rules. It avoids choosing formal or informal “you.” Wejście means entrance, and wyjście means exit.`, practice: [`Ask for one regular ticket.`,`Ask about reduced-price tickets.`,`Ask if photos are allowed.`,`Ask where the entrance is.`,`Make a short museum ticket conversation.`]},{day: 17, title: `Emergencies and Safety`, title_native: `Nagłe sytuacje i bezpieczeństwo`, focus: `Today you will learn emergency phrases for travel safety in Poland. These are important if you lose something, feel unsafe, or need urgent help.`, vocab: [{pl: `pomocy`, en: `help`, ipa: `/poh-MOH-tsih/`},{pl: `policja`, en: `police`, ipa: `/poh-LEET-syah/`},{pl: `lekarz`, en: `doctor`, ipa: `/LEH-kazh/`},{pl: `szpital`, en: `hospital`, ipa: `/SHPYEE-tal/`},{pl: `apteka`, en: `pharmacy`, ipa: `/ap-TEH-kah/`},{pl: `zgubiłem`, en: `I lost, male speaker`, ipa: `/zgoo-BEE-wem/`},{pl: `zgubiłam`, en: `I lost, female speaker`, ipa: `/zgoo-BEE-wam/`},{pl: `portfel`, en: `wallet`, ipa: `/PORT-fel/`},{pl: `telefon`, en: `phone`, ipa: `/teh-LEH-fon/`},{pl: `niebezpieczne`, en: `dangerous`, ipa: `/nyeh-bez-PYECH-neh/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Potrzebuję pomocy.`, en: `I need help.`, ipa: `/poh-tsheh-BOO-yeh poh-MOH-tsih/`},{pl: `Proszę zadzwonić po policję.`, en: `Please call the police.`, ipa: `/PROH-sheh zad-ZVOH-neech poh poh-LEET-syeh/`},{pl: `Potrzebuję lekarza.`, en: `I need a doctor.`, ipa: `/poh-tsheh-BOO-yeh LEH-kah-zhah/`},{pl: `Zgubiłem portfel.`, en: `I lost my wallet.`, ipa: `/zgoo-BEE-wem PORT-fel/`},{pl: `Zgubiłam telefon.`, en: `I lost my phone.`, ipa: `/zgoo-BEE-wam teh-LEH-fon/`},{pl: `To jest pilne.`, en: `This is urgent.`, ipa: `/toh yest PEEL-neh/`}], grammar: `Some past-tense forms change by speaker gender: zgubiłem is used by a male speaker, and zgubiłam by a female speaker. Potrzebuję means “I need” and is very useful in urgent situations. Keep emergency phrases short and clear.`, practice: [`Say you need help.`,`Say you need a doctor.`,`Say you lost your wallet.`,`Ask someone to call the police.`,`Create a short emergency exchange at a hotel desk.`]},{day: 18, title: `Pharmacy and Feeling Sick`, title_native: `Apteka i złe samopoczucie`, focus: `Learn how to ask for basic help at a pharmacy in Wrocław. You will describe common symptoms and ask for medicine.`, vocab: [{pl: `ból`, en: `pain`, ipa: `/bool/`},{pl: `głowa`, en: `head`, ipa: `/GWOH-vah/`},{pl: `brzuch`, en: `stomach`, ipa: `/bzhooKH/`},{pl: `gardło`, en: `throat`, ipa: `/GAR-dwoh/`},{pl: `kaszel`, en: `cough`, ipa: `/KAH-shel/`},{pl: `gorączka`, en: `fever`, ipa: `/goh-RONCH-kah/`},{pl: `lek`, en: `medicine`, ipa: `/lek/`},{pl: `tabletka`, en: `pill`, ipa: `/tah-BLET-kah/`},{pl: `zimno`, en: `cold`, ipa: `/ZHEEM-noh/`},{pl: `chory`, en: `sick`, ipa: `/KHOH-rih/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Boli mnie głowa.`, en: `My head hurts.`, ipa: `/BOH-lee mnyeh GWOH-vah/`},{pl: `Boli mnie brzuch.`, en: `My stomach hurts.`, ipa: `/BOH-lee mnyeh bzhooKH/`},{pl: `Mam gorączkę.`, en: `I have a fever.`, ipa: `/mam goh-RONCH-keh/`},{pl: `Mam kaszel.`, en: `I have a cough.`, ipa: `/mam KAH-shel/`},{pl: `Poproszę coś na ból gardła.`, en: `Something for a sore throat, please.`, ipa: `/poh-PROH-sheh tsohsh nah bool GAR-dwah/`},{pl: `Czy potrzebuję recepty?`, en: `Do I need a prescription?`, ipa: `/chih poh-tsheh-BOO-yeh reh-TSEP-tih/`}], grammar: `Boli mnie... means “... hurts me,” and it is the common Polish way to describe pain. Mam means “I have,” useful for symptoms like fever or cough. Coś na... means “something for...” when asking for medicine.`, practice: [`Say your head hurts.`,`Say you have a fever.`,`Ask for something for a sore throat.`,`Ask if you need a prescription.`,`Practice a pharmacy conversation with three symptoms.`]},{day: 19, title: `Weather and What to Wear`, title_native: `Pogoda i ubranie`, focus: `Today you will talk about weather in Zakopane, where mountain conditions can change quickly. These phrases help you plan your day.`, vocab: [{pl: `pogoda`, en: `weather`, ipa: `/poh-GOH-dah/`},{pl: `słońce`, en: `sun`, ipa: `/SWON-tseh/`},{pl: `deszcz`, en: `rain`, ipa: `/deshch/`},{pl: `śnieg`, en: `snow`, ipa: `/shnyek/`},{pl: `wiatr`, en: `wind`, ipa: `/vyatr/`},{pl: `ciepło`, en: `warm`, ipa: `/CHYEP-woh/`},{pl: `zimno`, en: `cold`, ipa: `/ZHEEM-noh/`},{pl: `chmury`, en: `clouds`, ipa: `/KHOO-mih/`},{pl: `parasol`, en: `umbrella`, ipa: `/pah-RAH-sol/`},{pl: `kurtka`, en: `jacket`, ipa: `/KOORT-kah/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Jaka jest pogoda?`, en: `What is the weather like?`, ipa: `/YAH-kah yest poh-GOH-dah/`},{pl: `Jest zimno.`, en: `It is cold.`, ipa: `/yest ZHEEM-noh/`},{pl: `Jest ciepło.`, en: `It is warm.`, ipa: `/yest CHYEP-woh/`},{pl: `Pada deszcz.`, en: `It is raining.`, ipa: `/PAH-dah deshch/`},{pl: `Pada śnieg.`, en: `It is snowing.`, ipa: `/PAH-dah shnyek/`},{pl: `Potrzebuję kurtki.`, en: `I need a jacket.`, ipa: `/poh-tsheh-BOO-yeh KOORT-kee/`}], grammar: `Polish often uses jest with weather adjectives: jest zimno, jest ciepło. For rain and snow, use pada: pada deszcz and pada śnieg. Weather words are practical for small talk and planning outdoor activities.`, practice: [`Ask what the weather is like.`,`Say it is cold.`,`Say it is raining.`,`Say you need a jacket.`,`Create a weather update for a mountain day.`]},{day: 20, title: `Making Plans with Someone`, title_native: `Robienie planów z kimś`, focus: `Learn how to suggest simple plans with a local or fellow traveler in Poznań. You will use phrases for invitations, times, and places.`, vocab: [{pl: `spotkanie`, en: `meeting`, ipa: `/spot-KAH-nyeh/`},{pl: `kawiarnia`, en: `café`, ipa: `/kah-VYAR-nyah/`},{pl: `restauracja`, en: `restaurant`, ipa: `/res-tow-RAH-tsyah/`},{pl: `park`, en: `park`, ipa: `/park/`},{pl: `spacer`, en: `walk`, ipa: `/SPAH-tser/`},{pl: `kino`, en: `cinema`, ipa: `/KEE-noh/`},{pl: `dzisiaj`, en: `today`, ipa: `/JEE-shy/`},{pl: `jutro`, en: `tomorrow`, ipa: `/YOO-troh/`},{pl: `razem`, en: `together`, ipa: `/RAH-zem/`},{pl: `może`, en: `maybe / can`, ipa: `/MOH-zheh/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Masz czas dzisiaj?`, en: `Do you have time today?`, ipa: `/mash chas JEE-shy/`},{pl: `Może kawa?`, en: `Maybe coffee?`, ipa: `/MOH-zheh KAH-vah/`},{pl: `Chcesz iść na spacer?`, en: `Do you want to go for a walk?`, ipa: `/khchesh eeshch nah SPAH-tser/`},{pl: `Spotkajmy się o szóstej.`, en: `Let’s meet at six.`, ipa: `/spot-KAI-mih shyeh oh SHOOS-tey/`},{pl: `Gdzie się spotkamy?`, en: `Where shall we meet?`, ipa: `/gdjyeh shyeh spot-KAH-mih/`},{pl: `Do zobaczenia.`, en: `See you.`, ipa: `/doh zoh-bah-CHEH-nyah/`}], grammar: `Masz czas? is informal and means “Do you have time?” Use it with people your age or people you know. Spotkajmy się means “let’s meet,” a useful phrase for making plans. O szóstej means “at six.”`, practice: [`Ask someone if they have time today.`,`Suggest coffee.`,`Suggest going for a walk.`,`Say “Let’s meet at six.”`,`Write a simple plan for tomorrow in Polish.`]},{day: 21, title: `Talking About Likes and Dislikes`, title_native: `Mówienie o upodobaniach`, focus: `Today you will express simple preferences while exploring restaurants and attractions in Warsaw. These phrases help you make conversations more personal.`, vocab: [{pl: `lubię`, en: `I like`, ipa: `/LOO-byeh/`},{pl: `nie lubię`, en: `I don’t like`, ipa: `/nyeh LOO-byeh/`},{pl: `kocham`, en: `I love`, ipa: `/KOH-kham/`},{pl: `wolę`, en: `I prefer`, ipa: `/VOH-leh/`},{pl: `muzyka`, en: `music`, ipa: `/MOO-zih-kah/`},{pl: `jedzenie`, en: `food`, ipa: `/yeh-DZEH-nyeh/`},{pl: `kawa`, en: `coffee`, ipa: `/KAH-vah/`},{pl: `piwo`, en: `beer`, ipa: `/PEE-voh/`},{pl: `wino`, en: `wine`, ipa: `/VEE-noh/`},{pl: `miasto`, en: `city`, ipa: `/MYAS-toh/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Lubię polskie jedzenie.`, en: `I like Polish food.`, ipa: `/LOO-byeh POL-skyeh yeh-DZEH-nyeh/`},{pl: `Nie lubię piwa.`, en: `I don’t like beer.`, ipa: `/nyeh LOO-byeh PEE-vah/`},{pl: `Kocham muzykę.`, en: `I love music.`, ipa: `/KOH-kham moo-ZIH-keh/`},{pl: `Wolę kawę.`, en: `I prefer coffee.`, ipa: `/VOH-leh KAH-veh/`},{pl: `Lubię to miasto.`, en: `I like this city.`, ipa: `/LOO-byeh toh MYAS-toh/`},{pl: `To mi się podoba.`, en: `I like this.`, ipa: `/toh mee shyeh poh-DOH-bah/`}], grammar: `Lubię means “I like,” and nie lubię means “I don’t like.” Polish often changes the noun after these verbs, but memorized phrases will serve you well. To mi się podoba is a natural way to say “I like this” when reacting to a place, object, or experience.`, practice: [`Say you like Polish food.`,`Say you prefer coffee.`,`Say you love music.`,`Say you do not like beer.`,`Make three personal preference sentences.`]},{day: 22, title: `Small Talk with Locals`, title_native: `Rozmowa towarzyska z miejscowymi`, focus: `Learn friendly small talk for meeting locals in Gdańsk. You will ask simple questions and respond naturally.`, vocab: [{pl: `skąd`, en: `from where`, ipa: `/skont/`},{pl: `mieszkam`, en: `I live`, ipa: `/MYESH-kam/`},{pl: `pracuję`, en: `I work`, ipa: `/prah-TSOO-yeh/`},{pl: `podróżuję`, en: `I travel`, ipa: `/poh-droo-ZHOO-yeh/`},{pl: `wakacje`, en: `vacation`, ipa: `/vah-KAH-tsyeh/`},{pl: `ładny`, en: `nice / pretty`, ipa: `/WAD-nih/`},{pl: `ciekawy`, en: `interesting`, ipa: `/chyeh-KAH-vih/`},{pl: `świetny`, en: `great`, ipa: `/SHFYEHT-nih/`},{pl: `trochę`, en: `a little`, ipa: `/TROH-kheh/`},{pl: `też`, en: `also / too`, ipa: `/tesh/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Skąd jesteś?`, en: `Where are you from?`, ipa: `/skont YES-tesh/`},{pl: `Jestem z Londynu.`, en: `I am from London.`, ipa: `/YES-tem z LON-dih-noo/`},{pl: `Mieszkam w Chicago.`, en: `I live in Chicago.`, ipa: `/MYESH-kam f shee-KAH-goh/`},{pl: `Podróżuję po Polsce.`, en: `I am traveling around Poland.`, ipa: `/poh-droo-ZHOO-yeh poh POLS-tseh/`},{pl: `To bardzo ładne miasto.`, en: `This is a very pretty city.`, ipa: `/toh BAR-dzoh WAD-neh MYAS-toh/`},{pl: `Mówię trochę po polsku.`, en: `I speak a little Polish.`, ipa: `/MOO-vyeh TROH-kheh poh POL-skoo/`}], grammar: `Po polsku means “in Polish,” while po Polsce means “around Poland.” These look similar but mean different things. Mówię trochę po polsku is a friendly phrase that often encourages patient responses.`, practice: [`Ask someone where they are from.`,`Say you are traveling around Poland.`,`Say you speak a little Polish.`,`Compliment the city.`,`Write a short small-talk exchange with a local.`]},{day: 23, title: `Phone, Internet, and Practical Tech`, title_native: `Telefon, internet i praktyczna technologia`, focus: `Today you will handle phone and internet needs in a Polish city. These phrases help at hotels, cafés, and mobile shops.`, vocab: [{pl: `telefon`, en: `phone`, ipa: `/teh-LEH-fon/`},{pl: `internet`, en: `internet`, ipa: `/EEN-ter-net/`},{pl: `hasło`, en: `password`, ipa: `/HAH-swoh/`},{pl: `Wi-Fi`, en: `Wi-Fi`, ipa: `/VAI-fai/`},{pl: `ładowarka`, en: `charger`, ipa: `/wah-doh-VAR-kah/`},{pl: `gniazdko`, en: `outlet`, ipa: `/GNYAZD-koh/`},{pl: `karta SIM`, en: `SIM card`, ipa: `/KAR-tah seem/`},{pl: `bateria`, en: `battery`, ipa: `/bah-TEH-ryah/`},{pl: `działa`, en: `it works`, ipa: `/JAH-wah/`},{pl: `nie działa`, en: `it does not work`, ipa: `/nyeh JAH-wah/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Jakie jest hasło do Wi-Fi?`, en: `What is the Wi-Fi password?`, ipa: `/YAH-kyeh yest HAH-swoh doh VAI-fai/`},{pl: `Czy jest tu gniazdko?`, en: `Is there an outlet here?`, ipa: `/chih yest too GNYAZD-koh/`},{pl: `Potrzebuję ładowarki.`, en: `I need a charger.`, ipa: `/poh-tsheh-BOO-yeh wah-doh-VAR-kee/`},{pl: `Mój telefon nie działa.`, en: `My phone does not work.`, ipa: `/mooy teh-LEH-fon nyeh JAH-wah/`},{pl: `Poproszę kartę SIM.`, en: `A SIM card, please.`, ipa: `/poh-PROH-sheh KAR-teh seem/`},{pl: `Internet jest wolny.`, en: `The internet is slow.`, ipa: `/EEN-ter-net yest VOL-nih/`}], grammar: `Do can mean “for” in practical phrases like hasło do Wi-Fi, “password for Wi-Fi.” Mój means “my” for masculine nouns like telefon. Nie działa is a very useful phrase for anything that is not working.`, practice: [`Ask for the Wi-Fi password.`,`Ask if there is an outlet nearby.`,`Say your phone does not work.`,`Ask for a SIM card.`,`Create a hotel lobby tech-help dialogue.`]},{day: 24, title: `Laundry and Daily Errands`, title_native: `Pranie i codzienne sprawy`, focus: `Learn practical daily-life phrases for a longer stay in Warsaw or Kraków. You will ask about laundry, cleaning, and basic services.`, vocab: [{pl: `pranie`, en: `laundry`, ipa: `/PRAH-nyeh/`},{pl: `pralka`, en: `washing machine`, ipa: `/PRAL-kah/`},{pl: `suszarka`, en: `dryer`, ipa: `/soo-SHAR-kah/`},{pl: `mydło`, en: `soap`, ipa: `/MIH-dwoh/`},{pl: `ręcznik`, en: `towel`, ipa: `/RENCH-neek/`},{pl: `pokój`, en: `room`, ipa: `/POH-kooy/`},{pl: `sprzątanie`, en: `cleaning`, ipa: `/spzhon-TAH-nyeh/`},{pl: `dzisiaj`, en: `today`, ipa: `/JEE-shy/`},{pl: `jutro`, en: `tomorrow`, ipa: `/YOO-troh/`},{pl: `usługa`, en: `service`, ipa: `/oo-SWOO-gah/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Gdzie jest pralnia?`, en: `Where is the laundry room?`, ipa: `/gdjyeh yest PRAL-nyah/`},{pl: `Czy mogę zrobić pranie?`, en: `Can I do laundry?`, ipa: `/chih MOH-geh ZROH-beech PRAH-nyeh/`},{pl: `Potrzebuję ręcznika.`, en: `I need a towel.`, ipa: `/poh-tsheh-BOO-yeh RENCH-nee-kah/`},{pl: `Czy można posprzątać pokój?`, en: `Can the room be cleaned?`, ipa: `/chih MOZH-nah poh-SPZHON-tach POH-kooy/`},{pl: `Jutro, proszę.`, en: `Tomorrow, please.`, ipa: `/YOO-troh PROH-sheh/`},{pl: `Ile kosztuje ta usługa?`, en: `How much does this service cost?`, ipa: `/EE-leh kosh-TOO-yeh tah oo-SWOO-gah/`}], grammar: `Czy mogę...? asks permission to do something yourself, while Czy można...? asks if something is possible or allowed more generally. Potrzebuję plus a noun means “I need...” and is helpful for hotel items. Longer stays require practical service vocabulary.`, practice: [`Ask where the laundry room is.`,`Ask if you can do laundry.`,`Say you need a towel.`,`Ask if the room can be cleaned tomorrow.`,`Create a short hotel errand conversation.`]},{day: 25, title: `Problems and Complaints Politely`, title_native: `Problemy i uprzejme skargi`, focus: `Learn how to explain problems calmly at a hotel, restaurant, or station. Today is about being clear without sounding rude.`, vocab: [{pl: `problem`, en: `problem`, ipa: `/PROH-blem/`},{pl: `hałas`, en: `noise`, ipa: `/HAH-was/`},{pl: `zimny`, en: `cold`, ipa: `/ZHEEM-nih/`},{pl: `brudny`, en: `dirty`, ipa: `/BROOD-nih/`},{pl: `zepsuty`, en: `broken`, ipa: `/zep-SOO-tih/`},{pl: `rachunek`, en: `bill`, ipa: `/rah-KHOO-nek/`},{pl: `błąd`, en: `mistake`, ipa: `/bwont/`},{pl: `pokój`, en: `room`, ipa: `/POH-kooy/`},{pl: `jedzenie`, en: `food`, ipa: `/yeh-DZEH-nyeh/`},{pl: `przepraszam`, en: `excuse me / sorry`, ipa: `/psheh-PRAH-sham/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Przepraszam, jest problem.`, en: `Excuse me, there is a problem.`, ipa: `/psheh-PRAH-sham yest PROH-blem/`},{pl: `Pokój jest zimny.`, en: `The room is cold.`, ipa: `/POH-kooy yest ZHEEM-nih/`},{pl: `To jest zepsute.`, en: `This is broken.`, ipa: `/toh yest zep-SOO-teh/`},{pl: `Na rachunku jest błąd.`, en: `There is a mistake on the bill.`, ipa: `/nah rah-KHOO-nkoo yest bwont/`},{pl: `Jedzenie jest zimne.`, en: `The food is cold.`, ipa: `/yeh-DZEH-nyeh yest ZHEEM-neh/`},{pl: `Czy można to naprawić?`, en: `Can this be fixed?`, ipa: `/chih MOZH-nah toh nah-PRAH-veech/`}], grammar: `Jest problem is direct but acceptable when said politely with przepraszam. Polish uses adjectives that change forms, but to jest zepsute is a flexible phrase for “this is broken.” Czy można to naprawić? is a practical and polite way to ask for a solution.`, practice: [`Politely say there is a problem.`,`Say the room is cold.`,`Say there is a mistake on the bill.`,`Ask if it can be fixed.`,`Write a polite complaint at a restaurant.`]},{day: 26, title: `Invitations and Social Courtesy`, title_native: `Zaproszenia i uprzejmość towarzyska`, focus: `Today you will learn phrases for accepting, declining, and thanking someone socially in Poland. These are useful with locals, hosts, and new friends.`, vocab: [{pl: `zaproszenie`, en: `invitation`, ipa: `/zah-proh-SHEH-nyeh/`},{pl: `dziękuję`, en: `thank you`, ipa: `/jen-KOO-yeh/`},{pl: `chętnie`, en: `gladly`, ipa: `/KHEN-tneh/`},{pl: `niestety`, en: `unfortunately`, ipa: `/nyeh-STEH-tih/`},{pl: `może`, en: `maybe`, ipa: `/MOH-zheh/`},{pl: `później`, en: `later`, ipa: `/POOZH-nyey/`},{pl: `dzisiaj`, en: `today`, ipa: `/JEE-shy/`},{pl: `jutro`, en: `tomorrow`, ipa: `/YOO-troh/`},{pl: `miło`, en: `nice`, ipa: `/MEE-woh/`},{pl: `gość`, en: `guest`, ipa: `/gohshch/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Dziękuję za zaproszenie.`, en: `Thank you for the invitation.`, ipa: `/jen-KOO-yeh zah zah-proh-SHEH-nyeh/`},{pl: `Chętnie.`, en: `Gladly.`, ipa: `/KHEN-tneh/`},{pl: `Niestety, nie mogę.`, en: `Unfortunately, I can’t.`, ipa: `/nyeh-STEH-tih nyeh MOH-geh/`},{pl: `Może później.`, en: `Maybe later.`, ipa: `/MOH-zheh POOZH-nyey/`},{pl: `Bardzo mi miło.`, en: `I’m very pleased.`, ipa: `/BAR-dzoh mee MEE-woh/`},{pl: `To bardzo miłe.`, en: `That is very kind.`, ipa: `/toh BAR-dzoh MEE-weh/`}], grammar: `Chętnie is a warm and simple way to accept an invitation. Niestety softens a refusal and helps you sound polite. Polish social courtesy often values direct thanks plus a respectful tone.`, practice: [`Thank someone for an invitation.`,`Accept with Chętnie.`,`Politely decline with Niestety, nie mogę.`,`Say “Maybe later.”`,`Create a short invitation dialogue.`]},{day: 27, title: `Talking About Travel Experiences`, title_native: `Mówienie o doświadczeniach z podróży`, focus: `Learn how to describe what you did and what you enjoyed while traveling through Poland. These phrases help you share stories with locals or other travelers.`, vocab: [{pl: `widziałem`, en: `I saw, male speaker`, ipa: `/vee-JAH-wem/`},{pl: `widziałam`, en: `I saw, female speaker`, ipa: `/vee-JAH-wam/`},{pl: `byłem`, en: `I was, male speaker`, ipa: `/BIH-wem/`},{pl: `byłam`, en: `I was, female speaker`, ipa: `/BIH-wam/`},{pl: `jadłem`, en: `I ate, male speaker`, ipa: `/YAD-wem/`},{pl: `jadłam`, en: `I ate, female speaker`, ipa: `/YAD-wam/`},{pl: `piękny`, en: `beautiful`, ipa: `/PYENK-nih/`},{pl: `ciekawy`, en: `interesting`, ipa: `/chyeh-KAH-vih/`},{pl: `podróż`, en: `journey / trip`, ipa: `/POH-droozh/`},{pl: `wrażenie`, en: `impression`, ipa: `/vrah-ZHEH-nyeh/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Byłem w Krakowie.`, en: `I was in Kraków.`, ipa: `/BIH-wem f KRAH-koh-vyeh/`},{pl: `Byłam w Warszawie.`, en: `I was in Warsaw.`, ipa: `/BIH-wam v var-SHAH-vyeh/`},{pl: `Widziałem zamek.`, en: `I saw the castle.`, ipa: `/vee-JAH-wem ZAH-mek/`},{pl: `Widziałam muzeum.`, en: `I saw the museum.`, ipa: `/vee-JAH-wam moo-ZEH-oom/`},{pl: `Jadłem pierogi.`, en: `I ate pierogi.`, ipa: `/YAD-wem pyeh-ROH-gee/`},{pl: `To było piękne.`, en: `It was beautiful.`, ipa: `/toh BIH-woh PYENK-neh/`}], grammar: `Past-tense verbs often change by speaker gender: byłem for a male speaker and byłam for a female speaker. The same pattern appears in widziałem/widziałam and jadłem/jadłam. These forms help you talk about travel memories naturally.`, practice: [`Say you were in Kraków.`,`Say you saw a castle.`,`Say you ate pierogi.`,`Say something was beautiful.`,`Write four sentences about yesterday’s travel day.`]},{day: 28, title: `More Natural Conversation Fillers`, title_native: `Bardziej naturalne wypełniacze rozmowy`, focus: `Today you will sound more natural in casual conversations in Poland. These short words help you react, pause, and keep a conversation moving.`, vocab: [{pl: `dobrze`, en: `well / okay`, ipa: `/DOH-bzheh/`},{pl: `jasne`, en: `sure / clear`, ipa: `/YAS-neh/`},{pl: `właśnie`, en: `exactly / just`, ipa: `/VWAHSH-nyeh/`},{pl: `naprawdę`, en: `really`, ipa: `/nah-PRAHV-deh/`},{pl: `chyba`, en: `probably / I think`, ipa: `/KHIH-bah/`},{pl: `oczywiście`, en: `of course`, ipa: `/oh-chih-VEESH-chyeh/`},{pl: `spoko`, en: `cool / no problem`, ipa: `/SPOH-koh/`},{pl: `świetnie`, en: `great`, ipa: `/SHFYEHT-nyeh/`},{pl: `rozumiem`, en: `I understand`, ipa: `/roh-ZOO-myem/`},{pl: `nie wiem`, en: `I don’t know`, ipa: `/nyeh vyem/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Jasne, rozumiem.`, en: `Sure, I understand.`, ipa: `/YAS-neh roh-ZOO-myem/`},{pl: `Naprawdę?`, en: `Really?`, ipa: `/nah-PRAHV-deh/`},{pl: `Nie wiem.`, en: `I don’t know.`, ipa: `/nyeh vyem/`},{pl: `Chyba tak.`, en: `I think so.`, ipa: `/KHIH-bah tahk/`},{pl: `Oczywiście.`, en: `Of course.`, ipa: `/oh-chih-VEESH-chyeh/`},{pl: `Świetnie, dziękuję.`, en: `Great, thank you.`, ipa: `/SHFYEHT-nyeh jen-KOO-yeh/`}], grammar: `Conversation fillers are short but powerful. Chyba softens a statement when you are not completely sure. Jasne and oczywiście both show agreement, but jasne is more casual.`, practice: [`React to surprising news with Naprawdę?`,`Say “I think so.”`,`Say “Sure, I understand.”`,`Use Nie wiem when you do not know an answer.`,`Add three fillers to a short Polish conversation.`]},{day: 29, title: `Handling Longer Questions`, title_native: `Radzenie sobie z dłuższymi pytaniami`, focus: `Learn survival phrases for when Polish speech feels too fast or complicated. These phrases help you stay in the conversation without panic.`, vocab: [{pl: `wolniej`, en: `more slowly`, ipa: `/VOL-nyey/`},{pl: `powtórzyć`, en: `repeat`, ipa: `/pof-TOO-zhihch/`},{pl: `rozumiem`, en: `I understand`, ipa: `/roh-ZOO-myem/`},{pl: `słowo`, en: `word`, ipa: `/SWOH-voh/`},{pl: `zdanie`, en: `sentence`, ipa: `/ZDAH-nyeh/`},{pl: `po polsku`, en: `in Polish`, ipa: `/poh POL-skoo/`},{pl: `po angielsku`, en: `in English`, ipa: `/poh ang-GYEL-skoo/`},{pl: `prosto`, en: `simply`, ipa: `/PROH-stoh/`},{pl: `jeszcze raz`, en: `one more time`, ipa: `/YESH-cheh raz/`},{pl: `łatwy`, en: `easy`, ipa: `/WAT-vih/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Proszę mówić wolniej.`, en: `Please speak more slowly.`, ipa: `/PROH-sheh MOO-veech VOL-nyey/`},{pl: `Proszę powtórzyć.`, en: `Please repeat.`, ipa: `/PROH-sheh pof-TOO-zhihch/`},{pl: `Jeszcze raz, proszę.`, en: `One more time, please.`, ipa: `/YESH-cheh raz PROH-sheh/`},{pl: `Nie rozumiem.`, en: `I don’t understand.`, ipa: `/nyeh roh-ZOO-myem/`},{pl: `Jak to powiedzieć po polsku?`, en: `How do you say that in Polish?`, ipa: `/yak toh poh-VYEH-jeech poh POL-skoo/`},{pl: `Czy może pan mówić po angielsku?`, en: `Can you speak English?`, ipa: `/chih MOH-zheh pahn MOO-veech poh ang-GYEL-skoo/`}], grammar: `Proszę plus an infinitive verb makes a polite request: Proszę mówić, Proszę powtórzyć. Nie rozumiem is simple and very useful. Asking Jak to powiedzieć po polsku? helps turn real conversations into lessons.`, practice: [`Ask someone to speak more slowly.`,`Ask someone to repeat.`,`Say you do not understand.`,`Ask how to say something in Polish.`,`Practice recovering from a fast conversation.`]},{day: 30, title: `Full Travel Day Review`, title_native: `Powtórka całego dnia podróży`, focus: `Today brings together greetings, transport, food, shopping, and help phrases for a complete day in Poland. Imagine spending a full day in Warsaw from breakfast to evening plans.`, vocab: [{pl: `podróż`, en: `trip / journey`, ipa: `/POH-droozh/`},{pl: `plan`, en: `plan`, ipa: `/plan/`},{pl: `śniadanie`, en: `breakfast`, ipa: `/shnya-DAH-nyeh/`},{pl: `obiad`, en: `lunch / dinner`, ipa: `/OH-byad/`},{pl: `kolacja`, en: `dinner / supper`, ipa: `/koh-LAH-tsyah/`},{pl: `bilet`, en: `ticket`, ipa: `/BEE-let/`},{pl: `centrum`, en: `center`, ipa: `/TSEN-troom/`},{pl: `hotel`, en: `hotel`, ipa: `/HOH-tel/`},{pl: `pomoc`, en: `help`, ipa: `/POH-mohts/`},{pl: `dziękuję`, en: `thank you`, ipa: `/jen-KOO-yeh/`}], phrases: [{pl: `Dzień dobry, mam rezerwację.`, en: `Good morning, I have a reservation.`, ipa: `/jen DOH-bri mam reh-zer-VAH-tsyah/`},{pl: `Poproszę kawę i śniadanie.`, en: `Coffee and breakfast, please.`, ipa: `/poh-PROH-sheh KAH-veh ee shnya-DAH-nyeh/`},{pl: `Gdzie jest przystanek do centrum?`, en: `Where is the stop to the center?`, ipa: `/gdjyeh yest pshih-STAH-nek doh TSEN-troom/`},{pl: `Poproszę bilet.`, en: `A ticket, please.`, ipa: `/poh-PROH-sheh BEE-let/`},{pl: `Czy może mi pan pomóc?`, en: `Can you help me?`, ipa: `/chih MOH-zheh mee pahn POH-moots/`},{pl: `To był świetny dzień.`, en: `That was a great day.`, ipa: `/toh biw SHFYEHT-nih jyen/`}], grammar: `By now, you can combine simple phrases into full travel interactions. Polish grammar has many endings, but polite fixed phrases work extremely well for travelers. Focus on clarity, tone, and practical vocabulary before perfection.`, practice: [`Create a morning hotel check-out exchange.`,`Order breakfast and coffee.`,`Ask for transport to the city center.`,`Ask someone politely for help.`,`Write six Polish sentences describing a full travel day.`]}];

var CONVERSATIONS_EN_PL = [{id: 1, title: `Ordering at a Café`, scene: `You are in a small café near Kraków’s Main Market Square. The barista greets you, and you order coffee and cake.`, lines: [{who: `them`, pl: `Dzień dobry, co podać?`, en: `Good morning, what can I get you?`},{who: `you`, pl: `Dzień dobry, poproszę małą kawę.`, en: `Good morning, a small coffee, please.`},{who: `them`, pl: `Z mlekiem czy bez mleka?`, en: `With milk or without milk?`},{who: `you`, pl: `Z mlekiem, ale bez cukru.`, en: `With milk, but without sugar.`},{who: `them`, pl: `Czy coś jeszcze?`, en: `Anything else?`},{who: `you`, pl: `Tak, poproszę kawałek ciasta.`, en: `Yes, a piece of cake, please.`},{who: `them`, pl: `Na miejscu czy na wynos?`, en: `For here or to go?`},{who: `you`, pl: `Na miejscu, proszę.`, en: `For here, please.`},{who: `them`, pl: `To będzie dwadzieścia złotych.`, en: `That will be twenty złoty.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Płacę kartą.`, en: `I’m paying by card.`},{who: `them`, pl: `Proszę bardzo.`, en: `Here you are.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Dziękuję bardzo.`, en: `Thank you very much.`}]},{id: 2, title: `Hotel Check-In`, scene: `You arrive at a hotel in Warsaw after a long train ride. The receptionist asks for your reservation and passport.`, lines: [{who: `them`, pl: `Dobry wieczór, witamy w hotelu.`, en: `Good evening, welcome to the hotel.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Dobry wieczór, mam rezerwację.`, en: `Good evening, I have a reservation.`},{who: `them`, pl: `Na jakie nazwisko?`, en: `Under what surname?`},{who: `you`, pl: `Na nazwisko Cannon.`, en: `Under the surname Cannon.`},{who: `them`, pl: `Poproszę paszport.`, en: `Your passport, please.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Proszę bardzo.`, en: `Here you are.`},{who: `them`, pl: `Śniadanie jest od siódmej do dziesiątej.`, en: `Breakfast is from seven to ten.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Dziękuję, czy jest winda?`, en: `Thank you, is there an elevator?`},{who: `them`, pl: `Tak, winda jest po prawej stronie.`, en: `Yes, the elevator is on the right side.`},{who: `you`, pl: `O której jest wymeldowanie?`, en: `What time is check-out?`},{who: `them`, pl: `Wymeldowanie jest o jedenastej.`, en: `Check-out is at eleven.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Świetnie, dziękuję.`, en: `Great, thank you.`}]},{id: 3, title: `Asking for Directions`, scene: `You are in Gdańsk and want to find the old town square. You stop a local person politely on the street.`, lines: [{who: `you`, pl: `Przepraszam, gdzie jest Stare Miasto?`, en: `Excuse me, where is the Old Town?`},{who: `them`, pl: `Stare Miasto jest blisko.`, en: `The Old Town is nearby.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Czy mogę iść pieszo?`, en: `Can I go on foot?`},{who: `them`, pl: `Tak, proszę iść prosto.`, en: `Yes, please go straight.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Prosto, a potem?`, en: `Straight, and then?`},{who: `them`, pl: `Potem w lewo przy moście.`, en: `Then left by the bridge.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Czy to daleko?`, en: `Is it far?`},{who: `them`, pl: `Nie, około dziesięć minut.`, en: `No, about ten minutes.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Dziękuję za pomoc.`, en: `Thank you for the help.`},{who: `them`, pl: `Nie ma za co.`, en: `You’re welcome.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Do widzenia.`, en: `Goodbye.`},{who: `them`, pl: `Do widzenia.`, en: `Goodbye.`}]},{id: 4, title: `At a Restaurant`, scene: `You are having dinner in a traditional restaurant in Poznań. You ask for the menu, order pierogi, and check whether the dish is spicy.`, lines: [{who: `them`, pl: `Dobry wieczór, stolik dla jednej osoby?`, en: `Good evening, a table for one person?`},{who: `you`, pl: `Tak, dziękuję.`, en: `Yes, thank you.`},{who: `them`, pl: `Proszę, tutaj jest menu.`, en: `Please, here is the menu.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Co pani poleca?`, en: `What do you recommend?`},{who: `them`, pl: `Polecam pierogi z serem i ziemniakami.`, en: `I recommend pierogi with cheese and potatoes.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Czy to jest ostre?`, en: `Is it spicy?`},{who: `them`, pl: `Nie, to nie jest ostre.`, en: `No, it is not spicy.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Dobrze, poproszę pierogi.`, en: `Good, pierogi, please.`},{who: `them`, pl: `Coś do picia?`, en: `Something to drink?`},{who: `you`, pl: `Poproszę wodę.`, en: `Water, please.`},{who: `them`, pl: `Oczywiście.`, en: `Of course.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Dziękuję bardzo.`, en: `Thank you very much.`}]},{id: 5, title: `Buying Train Tickets`, scene: `You are at a train station in Wrocław and want to travel to Kraków. You ask for a ticket and confirm the platform.`, lines: [{who: `them`, pl: `Dzień dobry, słucham.`, en: `Good morning, I’m listening.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Dzień dobry, poproszę bilet do Krakowa.`, en: `Good morning, a ticket to Kraków, please.`},{who: `them`, pl: `W jedną stronę czy powrotny?`, en: `One-way or return?`},{who: `you`, pl: `W jedną stronę, proszę.`, en: `One-way, please.`},{who: `them`, pl: `Pociąg odjeżdża o czternastej.`, en: `The train leaves at fourteen hundred.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Z którego peronu?`, en: `From which platform?`},{who: `them`, pl: `Z peronu trzeciego.`, en: `From platform three.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Czy pociąg jest opóźniony?`, en: `Is the train delayed?`},{who: `them`, pl: `Nie, jest punktualnie.`, en: `No, it is on time.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Ile kosztuje bilet?`, en: `How much does the ticket cost?`},{who: `them`, pl: `Sześćdziesiąt złotych.`, en: `Sixty złoty.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Dobrze, płacę kartą.`, en: `Good, I’m paying by card.`}]},{id: 6, title: `Shopping for Souvenirs`, scene: `You are in a souvenir shop in Toruń. You want to buy a T-shirt and ask about size, price, and payment.`, lines: [{who: `them`, pl: `Dzień dobry, czy mogę pomóc?`, en: `Good morning, can I help?`},{who: `you`, pl: `Dzień dobry, szukam pamiątki.`, en: `Good morning, I’m looking for a souvenir.`},{who: `them`, pl: `Mamy koszulki i kubki.`, en: `We have T-shirts and mugs.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Czy jest większy rozmiar?`, en: `Is there a larger size?`},{who: `them`, pl: `Tak, mamy rozmiar duży.`, en: `Yes, we have a large size.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Czy mogę przymierzyć?`, en: `Can I try it on?`},{who: `them`, pl: `Oczywiście, przymierzalnia jest tam.`, en: `Of course, the fitting room is there.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Dobrze, wezmę tę koszulkę.`, en: `Good, I’ll take this T-shirt.`},{who: `them`, pl: `To kosztuje czterdzieści złotych.`, en: `It costs forty złoty.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Płacę gotówką.`, en: `I’m paying cash.`},{who: `them`, pl: `Poproszę czterdzieści złotych.`, en: `Forty złoty, please.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Proszę, dziękuję.`, en: `Here you are, thank you.`}]},{id: 7, title: `At the Pharmacy`, scene: `You are in a pharmacy in Warsaw because your throat hurts. You explain your symptoms and ask whether you need a prescription.`, lines: [{who: `them`, pl: `Dzień dobry, w czym mogę pomóc?`, en: `Good morning, how can I help?`},{who: `you`, pl: `Dzień dobry, boli mnie gardło.`, en: `Good morning, my throat hurts.`},{who: `them`, pl: `Czy ma pan gorączkę?`, en: `Do you have a fever?`},{who: `you`, pl: `Nie, nie mam gorączki.`, en: `No, I don’t have a fever.`},{who: `them`, pl: `Czy ma pan kaszel?`, en: `Do you have a cough?`},{who: `you`, pl: `Tak, mam mały kaszel.`, en: `Yes, I have a small cough.`},{who: `them`, pl: `Polecam te tabletki.`, en: `I recommend these pills.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Czy potrzebuję recepty?`, en: `Do I need a prescription?`},{who: `them`, pl: `Nie, recepta nie jest potrzebna.`, en: `No, a prescription is not needed.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Poproszę jedno opakowanie.`, en: `One package, please.`},{who: `them`, pl: `Proszę bardzo.`, en: `Here you are.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Dziękuję bardzo.`, en: `Thank you very much.`}]},{id: 8, title: `Small Talk with a Local`, scene: `You meet a local person at a park in Łódź. You have a friendly conversation about travel, language, and the city.`, lines: [{who: `you`, pl: `Cześć, czy mogę usiąść tutaj?`, en: `Hi, can I sit here?`},{who: `them`, pl: `Tak, oczywiście.`, en: `Yes, of course.`},{who: `you`, pl: `Dziękuję, jestem turystą.`, en: `Thank you, I am a tourist.`},{who: `them`, pl: `Skąd jesteś?`, en: `Where are you from?`},{who: `you`, pl: `Jestem z USA i podróżuję po Polsce.`, en: `I am from the USA and I am traveling around Poland.`},{who: `them`, pl: `Jak ci się podoba Łódź?`, en: `How do you like Łódź?`},{who: `you`, pl: `Bardzo mi się podoba, to ciekawe miasto.`, en: `I like it very much; it is an interesting city.`},{who: `them`, pl: `Mówisz po polsku?`, en: `Do you speak Polish?`},{who: `you`, pl: `Mówię trochę po polsku.`, en: `I speak a little Polish.`},{who: `them`, pl: `Bardzo dobrze!`, en: `Very good!`},{who: `you`, pl: `Dziękuję, uczę się codziennie.`, en: `Thank you, I study every day.`},{who: `them`, pl: `Powodzenia i miłej podróży!`, en: `Good luck and have a nice trip!`}]}];